{
  "stem": "9987.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We found out that all the Jews were ordered to wear white armbands with blue Stars of David, so they can be recognized, that any time a Jew will be caught without wearing an armband, they'll be shot.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The German established Judenrats-- that means Jewish committees-- with presidents, with Jewish police.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And all the orders that the German wanted to give, they gave it through the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Jews had to go out every day to shovel the snow, to clean the streets, work on the airport, do all kind of work, without being paid.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In Krosno, the president of the Judenrat was a man that used to live all his life in Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But in 1938, as a Polish citizen living in Germany, he got thrown out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "His name was Engel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now, he was actually Jewish, but in--in his behavior, in everything else, he was a Nazi German.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Any time he used to talk to us, not like another Jew, but if he ordered something to do and you didn't want to do it, he used to call us the same way like the German used to called us, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That means you dog pigs, or pig dogs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I felt maybe I should make my life a little bit easier.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My friends joined the police, Jewish police, so I also wanted to join the Jewish police.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They didn't go out to work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They put somebody else to work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I come home and I say, I'm going to join the Jewish police.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there became a revolution in my house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I can imagine.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No way will you go and join the police.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I says, why not?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because we don't want any collaborator, German collaborator in our house.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
